{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":790,"text":"Twenty-three years ago,"},{"time":3395,"text":"at the age of 19,"},{"time":6150,"text":"I shot and killed a man."},{"time":9451,"text":"I was a young drug dealer"},{"time":11594,"text":"with a quick temper"},{"time":13963,"text":"and a semi-automatic pistol."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18018,"text":"But that wasn't the end of my story."},{"time":20789,"text":"In fact, it was beginning,"},{"time":24930,"text":"and the 23 years since"},{"time":27105,"text":"is a story of acknowledgment,"},{"time":30827,"text":"apology and atonement."},{"time":34310,"text":"But it didn't happen in the way"},{"time":35733,"text":"that you might imagine or think."},{"time":39027,"text":"These things occurred in my life"},{"time":40485,"text":"in a way that was surprising,"},{"time":42628,"text":"especially to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44263,"text":"See, like many of you,"},{"time":47404,"text":"growing up, I was an honor roll student,"},{"time":49978,"text":"a scholarship student,"},{"time":51321,"text":"with dreams of becoming a doctor."},{"time":53925,"text":"But things went dramatically wrong"},{"time":56556,"text":"when my parents separated"},{"time":58730,"text":"and eventually divorced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62567,"text":"The actual events are pretty straightforward."},{"time":65417,"text":"At the age of 17,"},{"time":67865,"text":"I got shot three times"},{"time":69510,"text":"standing on the corner of my block in Detroit."},{"time":74135,"text":"My friend rushed me to the hospital."},{"time":76830,"text":"Doctors pulled the bullets out,"},{"time":80054,"text":"patched me up,"},{"time":81845,"text":"and sent me back to the same \nneighborhood where I got shot."},{"time":86216,"text":"Throughout this ordeal,"},{"time":88971,"text":"no one hugged me,"},{"time":91031,"text":"no one counseled me,"},{"time":93401,"text":"no one told me I would be okay."},{"time":96341,"text":"No one told me that I would live in fear,"},{"time":99265,"text":"that I would become paranoid,"},{"time":101878,"text":"or that I would react hyper-violently"},{"time":104871,"text":"to being shot."},{"time":107249,"text":"No one told me that one day,"},{"time":110070,"text":"I would become the person behind the trigger."},{"time":114127,"text":"Fourteen months later,"},{"time":116801,"text":"at 2 a.m.,"},{"time":119411,"text":"I fired the shots"},{"time":121047,"text":"that caused a man's death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124900,"text":"When I entered prison,"},{"time":126810,"text":"I was bitter, I was angry, I was hurt."},{"time":132317,"text":"I didn't want to take responsibility."},{"time":135287,"text":"I blamed everybody from my parents"},{"time":137339,"text":"to the system."},{"time":140312,"text":"I rationalized my decision to shoot"},{"time":142524,"text":"because in the hood where I come from,"},{"time":144963,"text":"it's better to be the shooter"},{"time":146589,"text":"than the person getting shot."},{"time":149901,"text":"As I sat in my cold cell,"},{"time":153223,"text":"I felt helpless,"},{"time":154870,"text":"unloved and abandoned."},{"time":158257,"text":"I felt like nobody cared,"},{"time":162135,"text":"and I reacted"},{"time":164154,"text":"with hostility to my confinement."},{"time":167165,"text":"And I found myself getting"},{"time":168303,"text":"deeper and deeper into trouble."},{"time":170618,"text":"I ran black market stores,"},{"time":173398,"text":"I loan sharked,"},{"time":176117,"text":"and I sold drugs that were illegally smuggled"},{"time":178183,"text":"into the prison."},{"time":180044,"text":"I had in fact become"},{"time":181614,"text":"what the warden of the Michigan Reformatory called"},{"time":184295,"text":"\"the worst of the worst.\""},{"time":187132,"text":"And because of my activity,"},{"time":189457,"text":"I landed in solitary confinement"},{"time":192149,"text":"for seven and a half years"},{"time":194578,"text":"out of my incarceration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197790,"text":"Now as I see it, solitary confinement"},{"time":199459,"text":"is one of the most inhumane and barbaric places"},{"time":201399,"text":"you can find yourself,"},{"time":204298,"text":"but find myself I did."},{"time":207189,"text":"One day, I was pacing my cell,"},{"time":210700,"text":"when an officer came and delivered mail."},{"time":215217,"text":"I looked at a couple of letters"},{"time":216954,"text":"before I looked at the letter"},{"time":218868,"text":"that had my son's squiggly handwriting on it."},{"time":221930,"text":"And anytime I would get a letter from my son,"},{"time":223367,"text":"it was like a ray of light"},{"time":225272,"text":"in the darkest place you can imagine."},{"time":228029,"text":"And on this particular day, I opened this letter,"},{"time":231844,"text":"and in capital letters, he wrote,"},{"time":234950,"text":"\"My mama told me why you was in prison:"},{"time":238205,"text":"murder.\""},{"time":240899,"text":"He said, \"Dad, don't kill."},{"time":242818,"text":"Jesus watches what you do. Pray to Him.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":248265,"text":"Now, I wasn't religious at that time,"},{"time":250100,"text":"nor am I religious now,"},{"time":251807,"text":"but it was something so profound"},{"time":254291,"text":"about my son's words."},{"time":257063,"text":"They made me examine things about my life"},{"time":258685,"text":"that I hadn't considered."},{"time":260621,"text":"It was the first time in my life"},{"time":262557,"text":"that I had actually thought about the fact"},{"time":264529,"text":"that my son would see me as a murderer."},{"time":268195,"text":"I sat back on my bunk"},{"time":270249,"text":"and I reflected on something I had read"},{"time":272268,"text":"in [Plato],"},{"time":274865,"text":"where Socrates stated in \"Apology\""},{"time":276840,"text":"that the unexamined life isn't worth living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281111,"text":"At that point is when the transformation began."},{"time":286943,"text":"But it didn't come easy."},{"time":291920,"text":"One of the things I realized,"},{"time":293764,"text":"which was part of the transformation,"},{"time":295921,"text":"was that there were four key things."},{"time":299663,"text":"The first thing was,"},{"time":301970,"text":"I had great mentors."},{"time":304283,"text":"Now, I know some of you all are probably thinking,"},{"time":306159,"text":"how did you find a great mentor in prison?"},{"time":309328,"text":"But in my case,"},{"time":312193,"text":"some of my mentors"},{"time":313423,"text":"who are serving life sentences"},{"time":315300,"text":"were some of the best people\nto ever come into my life,"},{"time":318009,"text":"because they forced me to look at my life honestly,"},{"time":321273,"text":"and they forced me to challenge myself"},{"time":323098,"text":"about my decision making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325613,"text":"The second thing was literature."},{"time":329867,"text":"Prior to going to prison,"},{"time":331610,"text":"I didn't know that there were so many brilliant"},{"time":333607,"text":"black poets, authors and philosophers,"},{"time":336888,"text":"and then I had the great fortune"},{"time":339907,"text":"of encountering Malcolm X's autobiography,"},{"time":344074,"text":"and it shattered every\nstereotype I had about myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348621,"text":"The third thing was family."},{"time":351062,"text":"For 19 years, my father stood by my side"},{"time":355738,"text":"with an unshakable faith,"},{"time":358167,"text":"because he believed that I had what it took"},{"time":359831,"text":"to turn my life around."},{"time":362125,"text":"I also met an amazing woman"},{"time":365018,"text":"who is now the mother of\nmy two-year-old son Sekou,"},{"time":368452,"text":"and she taught me how to love myself"},{"time":370680,"text":"in a healthy way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374958,"text":"The final thing was writing."},{"time":377654,"text":"When I got that letter from my son,"},{"time":379068,"text":"I began to write a journal"},{"time":381278,"text":"about things I had experienced in my childhood"},{"time":384079,"text":"and in prison,"},{"time":386872,"text":"and what it did is it opened up my mind to the idea"},{"time":390138,"text":"of atonement."},{"time":393106,"text":"Earlier in my incarceration, I had received"},{"time":395188,"text":"a letter from one of the relatives of my victim,"},{"time":398995,"text":"and in that letter,"},{"time":401840,"text":"she told me she forgave me,"},{"time":403685,"text":"because she realized I was a young child"},{"time":405634,"text":"who had been abused"},{"time":406971,"text":"and had been through some hardships"},{"time":408763,"text":"and just made a series of poor decisions."},{"time":411501,"text":"It was the first time in my life"},{"time":413972,"text":"that I ever felt open to forgiving myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421701,"text":"One of the things that happened"},{"time":422945,"text":"after that experience is that"},{"time":425268,"text":"I thought about the other men who were incarcerated"},{"time":427156,"text":"alongside of me,"},{"time":428968,"text":"and how much I wanted to share this with them."},{"time":431890,"text":"And so I started talking to them about"},{"time":433644,"text":"some of their experiences,"},{"time":435571,"text":"and I was devastated to realize"},{"time":437053,"text":"that most of them came from\nthe same abusive environments,"},{"time":440431,"text":"And most of them wanted help\nand they wanted to turn it around,"},{"time":443970,"text":"but unfortunately the system"},{"time":445710,"text":"that currently holds 2.5 million people in prison"},{"time":448928,"text":"is designed to warehouse"},{"time":451128,"text":"as opposed to rehabilitate or transform."},{"time":455420,"text":"So I made it up in my mind"},{"time":457311,"text":"that if I was ever released from prison"},{"time":459065,"text":"that I would do everything in my power"},{"time":461522,"text":"to help change that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465223,"text":"In 2010, I walked out of prison"},{"time":467989,"text":"for the first time after two decades."},{"time":471067,"text":"Now imagine, if you will,"},{"time":472655,"text":"Fred Flintstone walking into an episode"},{"time":475237,"text":"of \"The Jetsons.\""},{"time":477620,"text":"That was pretty much what my life was like."},{"time":480555,"text":"For the first time, I was exposed to the Internet,"},{"time":483870,"text":"social media,"},{"time":485606,"text":"cars that talk like KITT from \"Knight Rider.\""},{"time":489743,"text":"But the thing that fascinated me the most"},{"time":491527,"text":"was phone technology."},{"time":493310,"text":"See, when I went to prison,"},{"time":494582,"text":"our car phones were this big"},{"time":496357,"text":"and required two people to carry them."},{"time":498958,"text":"So imagine what it was like when I first grabbed"},{"time":501046,"text":"my little Blackberry"},{"time":503172,"text":"and I started learning how to text."},{"time":505123,"text":"But the thing is, the people around me,"},{"time":506790,"text":"they didn't realize that I had no idea"},{"time":508386,"text":"what all these abbreviated texts meant,"},{"time":511080,"text":"like LOL, OMG, LMAO,"},{"time":516110,"text":"until one day I was having a conversation"},{"time":517852,"text":"with one of my friends via text,"},{"time":520108,"text":"and I asked him to do something,\nand he responded back, \"K.\""},{"time":524139,"text":"And I was like, \"What is K?\""},{"time":527318,"text":"And he was like, \"K is okay.\""},{"time":529280,"text":"So in my head, I was like,"},{"time":530279,"text":"\"Well what the hell is wrong with K?\""},{"time":533297,"text":"And so I text him a question mark."},{"time":535810,"text":"And he said, \"K = okay.\""},{"time":539481,"text":"And so I tap back, \"FU.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":544170,"text":"And then he texts back, and he asks me"},{"time":545926,"text":"why was I cussing him out."},{"time":547600,"text":"And I said, \"LOL FU,\""},{"time":550260,"text":"as in, I finally understand."},{"time":551959,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":553996,"text":"And so fast forward three years,"},{"time":557261,"text":"I'm doing relatively good."},{"time":559135,"text":"I have a fellowship at MIT Media Lab,"},{"time":561813,"text":"I work for an amazing company called BMe,"},{"time":565030,"text":"I teach at the University of Michigan,"},{"time":567360,"text":"but it's been a struggle"},{"time":569337,"text":"because I realize that there are more"},{"time":570800,"text":"men and women coming home"},{"time":572435,"text":"who are not going to be\nafforded those opportunities."},{"time":575596,"text":"I've been blessed to work with some amazing"},{"time":577401,"text":"men and women,"},{"time":580085,"text":"helping others reenter society,"},{"time":581847,"text":"and one of them is my friend named Calvin Evans."},{"time":586060,"text":"He served 24 years for a crime he didn't commit."},{"time":589015,"text":"He's 45 years old. He's currently enrolled in college."},{"time":592783,"text":"And one of the things that we talked about"},{"time":594507,"text":"is the three things that I found important"},{"time":596219,"text":"in my personal transformation,"},{"time":597839,"text":"the first being acknowledgment."},{"time":599778,"text":"I had to acknowledge that I had hurt others."},{"time":602204,"text":"I also had to acknowledge that I had been hurt."},{"time":605000,"text":"The second thing was apologizing."},{"time":607421,"text":"I had to apologize to the people I had hurt."},{"time":609571,"text":"Even though I had no expectations\nof them accepting it,"},{"time":611643,"text":"it was important to do because it was the right thing."},{"time":614395,"text":"But I also had to apologize to myself."},{"time":617354,"text":"The third thing was atoning."},{"time":620171,"text":"For me, atoning meant"},{"time":621854,"text":"going back into my community"},{"time":623447,"text":"and working with at-risk youth"},{"time":624990,"text":"who were on the same path,"},{"time":626790,"text":"but also becoming at one with myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630530,"text":"Through my experience of being locked up,"},{"time":632294,"text":"one of the things I discovered is this:"},{"time":634475,"text":"the majority of men and women"},{"time":635691,"text":"who are incarcerated are redeemable,"},{"time":639112,"text":"and the fact is,"},{"time":640372,"text":"90 percent of the men and\nwomen who are incarcerated"},{"time":642723,"text":"will at some point return to the community,"},{"time":645411,"text":"and we have a role in determining what kind"},{"time":647326,"text":"of men and women return to our community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650945,"text":"My wish today"},{"time":653556,"text":"is that we will embrace"},{"time":657209,"text":"a more empathetic approach"},{"time":659358,"text":"toward how we deal with mass incarceration,"},{"time":662578,"text":"that we will do away with"},{"time":663722,"text":"the lock-them-up-and-throw-away-the-key mentality,"},{"time":666037,"text":"because it's proven it doesn't work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669960,"text":"My journey is a unique journey,"},{"time":672413,"text":"but it doesn't have to be that way."},{"time":675078,"text":"Anybody can have a transformation"},{"time":677484,"text":"if we create the space for that to happen."},{"time":680324,"text":"So what I'm asking today"},{"time":682086,"text":"is that you envision"},{"time":683793,"text":"a world where men and women"},{"time":686133,"text":"aren't held hostage to their pasts,"},{"time":689829,"text":"where misdeeds and mistakes"},{"time":691262,"text":"don't define you for the rest of your life."},{"time":694030,"text":"I think collectively, we can create that reality,"},{"time":697221,"text":"and I hope you do too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698924,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700690,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}